## Pattern 5: Empty Block Statements

**Warning:** `Empty block statement.`

### Add Comment or Handling

```javascript
// ❌ WRONG: Empty catch block
try {
  await optionalOperation();
} catch (e) {
}

// ✅ CORRECT: Explain why empty
try {
  await optionalOperation();
} catch (e) {
  // Intentionally ignored - this operation is optional and failure is acceptable
}

// ✅ BETTER: Add logging
try {
  await optionalOperation();
} catch (e) {
  console.debug('Optional operation skipped:', e.message);
}

// ✅ BEST: Use conditional instead of empty catch
const result = await optionalOperation().catch(() => null);
if (result) {
  processResult(result);
}
```

